title: Political career of Donald Trump
added: Trump’s involvement in politics began in the late 1970s and early 80s when he donated to the presidential campaigns of Ronald Reagan, Jimmy Carter, and later a PAC affiliated with Walter Mondale. Between 1982 and 1985, he would be involved in fundraising and financing for the Vietnam Veterans Plaza as co-chair of the Vietnam Veterans Memorial Commission, hosting of the 1983 National Awards Banquet Dinner as a special advisor to the President’s Council on Physical Fitness and Sport, and overseeing the body’s work and fundraising activities.
